definition.value: A trichlorophenol carrying chloro groups at positions 2, 4 and 5.
A biflavonoid isolated from the seeds of Garcinia kola that has been shown to exhibit hepatoprotective activity.
An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 4-hydroxybutyric acid.
A member of the class of dihydrochalcones that is dihydrochalcone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2' and 6' and a methoxy group at position 4' respectively.
A D-galactose 6-sulfate that has alpha configuration at the anomeric centre.
Lipid IVA glycosylated with two 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonic acid (KDO) residues.
A rutinoside that is quercetin with the hydroxy group at position C-3 substituted with glucose and rhamnose sugar groups.
An oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxylic acid group of 3-oxodecanoic acid.
A quercetin O-glucoside in which a glucosyl residue is attached at position 7 of quercetin via a beta-glycosidic linkage.
A germacranolide isolated from Laurus nobilis L..
A GDP-hexose compound having 6-deoxy-L-xylo-hexopyranosyl-4-ulose as the hexose fragment.
A cholestanoyl-CoA formed by thioester linkage between 3alpha,7alpha-dihydroxy-24-oxo-5beta-cholestan-26-oic acid and coenzyme A.
A bromoalkane that is ethane carrying bromo substituents at positions 1 and 2. It is produced by marine algae.
An oxindole that is 1,3-dihydro-2H-indol-2-one substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3.
A retinal which contains an additional double bond between the 3 and 4 positions of the six-membered ring, and in which all of the double bonds in the side chain have the E-configuration.

A sialodiosylceramide consisting of the pentasaccharide alpha-Neu5NAc-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5NAc-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5NAc-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide.
A 2-deoxyribose 1-phosphate with D-ribofuranose as the sugar. An intermediate in the metabolism of pyrimidine.
A D-lyxopyranose with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric position.

A cardenolide glycoside in which the 3beta-hydroxy group of digitoxigenin carries a 2,6-dideoxy-beta-D-ribo-hexopyranosyl-(1->4)-2,6-dideoxy-beta-D-ribo-hexopyranosyl-(1->4)-2,6-dideoxy-beta-D-ribo-hexopyranosyl trisaccharide chain.
A twelve-membered cyclodepsipeptide composed of three repeating D-alpha-hydroxyisovaleryl-D-valyl-L-lactoyl-L-valyl units joined in sequence. An antibiotic found in several Streptomyces strains.

A  primary arylamine that is the derivative of aniline in which the hydrogen at position 4 has been substituted by fluorine. It is used as an intermediate in the manufacture of pharmaceuticals, herbicides and plant growth regulators.
A carbohydrate acid derivative anion arising from selective deprotonation of the carboxy function of D-glucuronic acid 1-phosphate.
The D-enantiomer of pinitol.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is 2-oxobutyric acid which is substituted at position 3 by an indol-3-yl group.
A D-ribulose with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric position.
A hexasaccharide that is verbascose which has an additional unit of alpha-D-galactopyranose attached by a 1->6 glycosidic linkage to the terminal galactosyl residue.
A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is biochanin A 7-O-beta-D-glucoside in which the hydroxy group at position 6 of the glucosyl moiety has been acylated by one of the carboxy groups of malonic acid.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of cyclohexane-1-carboxylic acid.
beta-Limit dextrin is the remaining polymer produced by enzymatic hydrolyse of amylopectine with beta amylase which cannot hydrolyse the alpha-1,6 bonds at branch points.
A multi-methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of farnesoic acid.
A D-mannopyranose in which the anomeric centre has beta configuration.
A member of the class of  hydroxyfluorenes that is 9H-fluorene substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 2.
An azacycloalkane that consists of a six-membered ring containing two nitrogen atoms at opposite positions.

A stilbenoid that is ethane in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a 4-hydroxyphenyl group and one of the hydrogens of the remaining methyl group is replaced by a 4-hydroxy-3,5-dimethoxyphenyl group.
An (R)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (R)-3-hydroxyoctanoic acid.
